Others: Stephen Curry returned to form with a season-high 24 points on 7-15 shooting from the field.
The Warriors held Jordan Poole to 2-10 shooting from three-point range and a minus-nine on the affair.
Bilal Coulibaly was limited to a season-low nine points on 3-11 shooting from the field.
The Warriors won the rebounding battle 56-47 and held the Wizards to 23 percent shooting from distance.
Andrew Wiggins struggled mightily, managing to score only five points on a putrid 1-9 shooting overall.

Draymond Green, Buddy Hield, and Jonathan Kuminga fulfilled their roles to a tee, with Green pitching in 18 points, eight rebounds, and five assists, Hield scoring 20 points, five rebounds, and three triples, and Kuminga scoring a strong 15 points on 7-15 shooting from the field.
